				<p>Why do I care? I have seen stroke victims as young as 38 being brought into a hospital ER. I wish someone had just checked these 3 simple markers and informed them of the elevated risks of stroke. Some of these risk factors can be fixed within days.  </p>
				<h3>What are the Three Triggers of Stroke?</h3>
				<p>I'm sure you're wondering, so what exactly are the three sisters of stroke? How do you identify them and, more importantly, prevent strokes? You'll be surprised to see that these three Triggers of strokes are pretty standard and defined by the American Heart Association. They are:</p>
				<ul>
					<li><strong>High Blood Pressure:</strong> High blood pressure significantly increases chances of stroke.</li>
					<li><strong>High Central Obesity:</strong> Obesity with particularly a wide waist, along with high blood pressure.</li>
					<li><strong>High Triglycerides:</strong> From the common cholesterol blood test called Lipid profile.</li>
				</ul>
				<p>I never knew the 3 risk factors above, when combined together, means you need to watch out for strokes. You should remedy this immediately.</p>

				<h3>HOW TO REDUCE RISK FACTORS:</h3>
				<p><strong>High Blood Pressure:</strong> Blood pressure should be brought down quickly with the right medications. The long term solution is to reduce blood pressure from the source and not need medications (because they have side effects) but we suggest to immediately remedy high blood pressure with medications.</p>
